My train of thought was following:
1. vote result represents opinion of &quot;masses&quot;
2. the comment in question says &quot;masses of people need a clear, obvious Right Thing&quot;
3. the comment itself is not clear and obvious as it contains double bind (asks to consider to be inconsiderate)
4. comment got downvoted which confirms #2<p>Just our of curiosity I&#x27;ve replied with another double bind &quot;downvotes proof comment worthiness&quot; which seems have reversed the trend.<p>Speaking on topic, I think that choosing between Right Thing and Full Picture for the &quot;masses&quot; is like choosing between acceleration and breaks for a car: it is better to have both. Right Thing mobilizes masses while Full Picture helps to avoid dumb aggression.

